{{Infobox organization | name = Finnish Orienteering Federation | logo =Finnish Orienteering Federation.png | type = Orienteering club | founded_date = 1945 | founder = | location = [[Helsinki]] | origins = | key_people = | area_served = [[Finland]] | product = | focus = | method = | revenue = | endowment = | num_volunteers = | num_employees = | num_members = | subsib = | owner = | Non-profit_slogan = | homepage = [http://www.ssl.fi/ http://www.ssl.fi/] | dissolved = | footnotes = }} The '''Finnish Orienteering Federation''' ({{lang-fi|Suomen Suunnistusliitto, SSL}}, {{lang-sv|Finlands Orienteringsförbund}}) is the governing body for the sport of [[orienteering]] in [[Finland]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fin5.fi/SSL/sslweb.nsf/sp?open&cid=eng |title=The Finnish Orienteering Federation |accessdate=2008-05-25 |publisher=fin5.fi |date=May 25, 2008 }}</ref> The federation was founded in 1945 and has approximately 60,000 members.<ref name="uppslagsverketfinland">"[https://www.uppslagsverket.fi/sv/sok/view-103684-Orientering orientering]", [[Uppslagsverket Finland]]. Last updated 2016-05-26. Retrieved 2018-11-17.</ref>
The Finnish Orienteering Federation publishes the orienteering magazine ''Suunnistaja''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.suunnistusliitto.fi/the-finnish-orienteering-federation/|title =Finnish Orienteering Federation|accessdate=15 April 2015}}</ref>
==History== The Finnish Orienteering Federation was among the ten founding members of IOF in 1961.<ref name=o1987>{{cite book |title=Orienteringsidretten i Norge gjennom 90 år |editor=Knut Berglia |editor2=Tom-Erik Brohaug |editor3=Kristoffer Staver |editor4=Kaare Thuesen |editor5=Torgeir Strandhagen |language=Norwegian |year=1987 |publisher=[[Norges Orienteringsforbund]]|pages=159, 278 }}</ref> Finland hosted the very first [[World Orienteering Championships]], in 1966.<ref>Berglia 1957 pp. 203&ndash;204</ref>
The Finnish female team won gold medals in the relay at the 1972, 1978, 1979, 1995, 2001, 2006, 2007, 2008, 2010 and 2011 world championships, and the men's relay team won a gold medal in 2001, and silver medals in 1966, 1968, 1974, 1979, 1995, 1997, 1999, 2003 and 2006. Among Finnish individual world champions in foot orienteering are [[Kari Sallinen]], [[Jani Lakanen]], [[Janne Salmi]], [[Pasi Ikonen]], [[Mårten Boström]], [[Liisa Veijalainen]], [[Outi Borgenström-Anjala]], [[Kirsi Boström]], [[Minna Kauppi]] and [[Heli Jukkola]].
