{{Infobox stadium | name = Galt Arena Gardens | nickname = | image = Galt Arena Gardens exterior.jpg | image_size = 220 | caption = Front facade of Galt Arena Gardens | fullname = | location = 98 Shade St., Cambridge, Ontario | coordinates = {{coord|43|21|47|N|80|18|23|W|type:landmark_region:CA-ON|display=inline,title}} | broke_ground = 1921 | built = | opened = January 1922 | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = mechanically frozen ice | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = | seating_capacity = 1,100 | dimensions = 200 ft x 80 ft (surface) }}
The '''Galt Arena Gardens''' is one of the oldest continuously-operating [[ice hockey]] arena in the world{{sfn|Rutherford|2012|p=61}} and the oldest operating [[arena]] in [[Ontario]]. Galt Arena Gardens was built throughout 1921 and opened in January 1922. It is located in the city of Galt, which is now a part of the city of [[Cambridge, Ontario|Cambridge]], [[Ontario]]. It is the home of the junior hockey team, [[Cambridge Winter Hawks]] as well as the [[Special Hockey International]] team, Cambridge Ice Hounds. The arena is noted for its impressive external [[facade]]. [[ice hockey|Hockey]] legend [[Gordie Howe]] played a season in the arena for the [[Galt Red Wings]] before playing in the [[National Hockey League]]. Former [[New York Americans]] centreman [[Norman Himes]] grew up right across the street from the arena at 91 Shade Street. He played [[Ontario Hockey Association|OHA]] senior hockey in the arena for the [[Galt Terriers]]. [[Ontario Hockey League|Ontario Hockey Association]] teams including the [[Galt Rockets]] and [[Galt Black Hawks]] also played at the building.
Several ice hockey arenas are older, including the [[Aberdeen Pavilion]] in [[Ottawa]], built in 1898, and the [[Stannus Street Rink]], of [[Windsor, Nova Scotia]], built in 1897, but are no longer in operation for ice hockey. The 1910 [[Matthews Arena]] in [[Boston]] is still in operation, but it closed for several seasons due to fires and for renovations.{{sfn|Rutherford|2012|p=62}}
The arena was most recently renovated in 1997, replacing the concrete floor, the spectator seating and the dressing rooms.{{sfn|Rutherford|2012|p=62}} The renovation reduced [[seating capacity]] from 2,000 to 1,100.
