{{Infobox National Olympic Committee | title = National Olympic Committee of the Republic of Tajikistan | logo = National Olympic Committee of the Republic of Tajikistan logo.svg | size = 150px | country = Tajikistan | code = TJK | created = 1992 | recognized = 1993 | association = OCA | headquarters = [[Dushanbe]], [[Tajikistan]] | president = [[Emomalii Rahmon]] | secretary general = [[Bahrullo Radhzabaliev]] | website = [http://www.olympic.tj/ www.olympic.tj] }} The '''National Olympic Committee of the Republic of Tajikistan''' (NOC) is a sports governing body that was established in 1992 to manage [[Tajikistan|Tajikistan's]] activities in relation to the [[Olympics]]. The office of the NOC is located in the center of the city, on [[Sadriddin Aini|Aini]] Street in [[Dushanbe]].
The current [[National Olympic Committee]] of Tajikistan is headed by [[Bakhrullo Radzhabaliev]] (President) and [[Shirinjon Mamadsafoev]] (Secretary General).<ref>[http://www.olympic.org/uk/organisation/noc/noc_uk.asp?noc_initials=TJK International Olympic Committee - Organisation - Structures<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
Tajikistan made its debut as an independent nation at the [[1996 Olympic Games]] in [[Atlanta]], [[United States]]. The most recent Olympics in [[2008 Beijing Olympic Games|Beijing 2008]] marked the country's fourth appearance and first [[Olympic Medals|Olympic medal]] wins, with [[Rasul Boqiev]] winning bronze in the [[Judo]] under 73&nbsp;kg category and [[Yusup Abdusalomov]] winning the silver medal in the [[freestyle wrestling]] under 84&nbsp;kg category.
