'''Pakistan Customs cricket team''' were a [[first-class cricket]] side of no fixed abode that played in domestic tournaments in [[Pakistan]] from 1972-73 to 2009-10, representing the [[Pakistan Customs]] service. They never won the [[Quaid-e-Azam Trophy]], but did win the [[Patron's Trophy]] once.
They played 122 matches, with 25 wins, 56 losses and 41 draws.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Records/Pakistan/Firstclass/PakistanCustoms/Team_Records/Playing_Record.html Pakistan Customs playing record]</ref> Their highest score, and only double century, was 210 not out by [[Imraan Mohammad]] against [[Gujranwala cricket team|Gujranwala]] in 1999-2000.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Records/Pakistan/Firstclass/PakistanCustoms/Batting_Records/Highest_Innings_For.html Highest score for Pakistan Customs]</ref> Their best innings bowling figures were 8 for 64 by Nadeem Iqbal against [[Habib Bank Limited cricket team|Habib Bank Limited]] in 1998-99.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Records/Pakistan/Firstclass/PakistanCustoms/Bowling_Records/Best_Innings_Bowling_For.html Best bowling figures for Pakistan Customs]</ref>
[[Image:Fawad alam.jpg|150px|right|thumb|Pakistan Customs cricketer [[Fawad Alam]]]]
