{{Infobox stadium | name = Wellness and Events Center | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Newark, New Jersey]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = November 12, 2015<ref name="Ground Breaking"/> | built = | opened = | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = [[New Jersey Institute of Technology]] | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = [[United States dollar|US$]]110,000,000<ref name="NJIT Bond Issue for Center">{{cite web|title=RESOLUTION OF THE BOARD OF TR USTEES OF NEW JERSEY INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY AUTHORIZING THE ISSUANCE OF GENERAL OBLIGATION BONDS, 2015 SERIES A|url=http://www.njit.edu/about/boards/trustees/pdf/2015/2015-03-08-bond-resolution-2015-series-A.pdf|publisher=NJIT.edu|accessdate=12 November 2015}}</ref> | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 3,500 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = 200,000 sqft<ref>{{cite web|title=NJIT plans $100M events center, may help NCAA Conference discussion|url=http://www.nj.com/essex/index.ssf/2015/02/njit_plans_100m_events_center_may_help_ncaa_confer.html|publisher=nj.com|accessdate=12 November 2015}}</ref> | acreage = | volume = | tenants = [[NJIT Highlanders]] | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }}
The '''Wellness and Events Center''' ('''WEC''') is a 3,500 seat basketball arena in [[Newark, New Jersey]]. It was built at a cost of [[United States dollar|US$]]102,000,000 by the [[New Jersey Institute of Technology]].<ref name="NJIT Bond Issue for Center"/><ref>{{cite web|title=NJIT Breaks Grounds On a Major New Building: The Wellness and Events Center|url=http://www.njit.edu/features/sceneandheard/wec.php|publisher=NJIT.edu|accessdate=12 November 2015}}</ref> The Wellness and Events Center is the home court of the [[NJIT Highlanders]], which as of the [[2015–16 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2015–16 season]] became members of the [[Atlantic Sun Conference]]. It replaced the former arena of the Highlanders, the [[Fleisher Center]]. The new arena broke ground on November 12, 2015 and opened in time for the [[2017–18 NJIT Highlanders men's basketball team|2017–18]] basketball season.<ref name="Ground Breaking">{{cite web|title=NJIT breaks ground on $100M Wellness and Events Center|url=http://www.app.com/story/sports/college/2015/11/12/njit-breaks-ground-100m-wellness-and-events-center/75609258/|publisher=app.com|accessdate=12 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nj.com/essex/index.ssf/2017/11/we_dont_have_anything_like_this_njit_unveils_110m.html|title='We don't have anything like this.' NJIT unveils $110M athletic center|website=NJ.com|date=November 11, 2017|accessdate=December 26, 2017}}</ref>
